====Definitions====
{{zh-hanzi}}

# {{lb|zh|Beginning Mandarin}} {{non-gloss definition|Used after a verb, indicate [[perfective aspect]] (action completion)}}
#: {{zh-usex|我 吃 了 這 個 蘋果。|I '''ate''' the apple.}}
# {{non-gloss definition|Used at the end of a sentence, indicate a change of state.}}
#: {{zh-usex|他 是 大學生 了。|He '''has become''' student / He is a student '''now'''}}
# ({{non-gloss definition|Used after a verb and followed by an amount of time, express duration}}) [[for]]
#: {{zh-usex|他 在 ^北京 住 '''了''' 兩 年。|He lived in Beijing '''for''' two years.}}

====Usage notes====
* {{sense|perfective aspect particle}}
: Most of the time, 了 is translated by a [[past tense]]. But it can also indicate that one action is completed before another.
: {{zh-usex|你 吃 '''了''' 以後，告訴{su} 我。|Tell me when you are done eating.|in_notes=1}}

* {{sense|change of state particle}}
: When used as the ''change of state particle'', 了 can be translated by [[now]], [[already]] or not [[anymore]].
: {{zh-usex|我 會 說 中文 '''了'''。|I can speak Chinese '''now'''. (I couldn't before)|in_notes=1}}
: {{zh-usex|我 吃飯 '''了'''。|I've eaten ('''already''').|in_notes=1}}
: {{zh-usex|沒有 紙 '''了'''。|There's no paper '''anymore'''.|in_notes=1}}

: In a question, 了 is put before the particle {{zh-l|嗎/吗}}.

